title: For Sale:  Thomas Kinkade Lilac Gezebo
postcontent: I have for sale a Thomas Kinkades Lilac Gazebo Gallery Proof number 162 of 715. If you research the internet for the real thing, not some photocopy and if you can even find a GP lithograph under #500 your not going to touch this for anything less than $350 and that is the print alone. I purchased this along with 3 other pieces before Thomas Kinkade passed away from one of his Galleries in California. The one thing that lets the buyer know that the Gallery Proof is the real thing is the little gold emblem that is on each Gallery Proof that is made. These emblems very per piece and usually have some significant to his family of something in the painting. My wife and I had this professionally streached & framed by Hobby Lobby and spared no expense having this done. We ordered custom glass that protects the art from UV light and kept with Thomas Kinkades frame style with real wood and his triple matting that his framed art is known for. We also has a custom metal tag with the art piece title included when the framing was done.  The price I am asking will basically cover the cost of the frame. Unfortunate times force some of us to have to get rid of things in order to get buy and my hope is that this will make someone very happy and allow them to enjoy a real nice piece from his work. This Gallery Proof only came in 16x12 and hence, with the frame, the piece is much larger. The picture I am posting in this post is of the same titled piece of work that I am selling framed. I will be more than happy to send you some pictures of the actual art once we have made contact with one another via email/phone. Just a little (FYI) Lilac Gazebo was release by Kinkade in 1996 and to this day is rated as one of the top 10 most sought after pieces people want. Please feel free to contact me via phone call at (765 two-seven- four 5056) at any time. I live close to Highway 69 and the closest exit to me is exit 214 Lapel Indiana. I have no problem meeting someone within reason. Public places such as a gas station, place to eat, etc.. off an exit seems to be a good meeting place or if you would like to view this at my location we can set up a time without a problem. I would also encourage you to call around to some of the local Thomas Kinkade Galleries and ask them what this particular piece is worth. If you do, be sure to include the fact that it is a G/P along with the # edition etc. I look forward to meeting with whoever becomes the new owner of this as I know you will enjoy it. If you are looking for something a bit larger, we are considering selling our largest peice which is 32''x40'' and is a canvas GP "Rose Garden.....This one however needs it's own wall, if you are interested in this one, please drop me a line and let me know. Thanks to all who look and consider. With Christmas on it's way very close, this will make a wonderful gift. A last bit of information, we do have an actual Thomas Kinkade Gallary in Zionsille Indiana if anyone would like to contact them for info, value, price etc.....
